180,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d528363-Reviews-or180-Tony_s_House_Hotel-London_England.html#REVIEWS,"Tony's House Hotel Reviews, London",Not that bad!,"After reading the sole post on this hotel, I figured I'd better add my 2-pence worth.  Me, my wife, and two grown children stayed at Tonys during July 2004.  It was not great, but it was adequate.  We had a quad at the front on the first floor, overlooking the square, with a new, modular bathroom.  No odors or similar problems in our room.  We were there for 3 nights, and yes - sheets were not changed.  Like many budget hotels in London, it is old, but we found it to be clean.  Sorry to hear about the rats; we saw no evidence of rodents or other vermin.  Good location, near Hyde Park.  Continental rather than English breakfast, but it was adequate.  I can recommend Tony's to the traveler looking for a budget hotel in London. ",Date of stay: July 2004,3.0
